Text.Value: *Low!*
There's something strange about this ox. What is it?
*Hnr!*
Moo!

EditorData.NodeContext: Spoken by the ox (i.e. no SFX); a phasm pretending to be a normal ox.

Text.Value: Whatever your secret is, it's yours to keep.
Now - that's all I have to say besides - and I really mean this - moo.
Out with it, cow, or you're going to regret it.
A pitiful lie. Scurry along now, before something dreadful happens to you.
*Snuff!*
Ohoho, I'd so love to see them try.
Haven't you ever met anyone who could speak to oxen?
A fine looking beast you are.
Moo.

EditorData.NodeContext: Spoken by the ox (i.e. no SFX); a phasm pretending to be a normal ox.

Text.Value: *Moo!*
Fine. I heard the tieflings are going to butcher one of you for food, so your secret will die with you.
No. You are... incapable.
Tee-hee.
Leave.
A druid or two, I suppose. But the novelty remains fresh.
I'll tell you this much: I'm going to Baldur's Gate. With or without the rest of these poor sods.
Leave.
Ugh. Hideous cow.
You don't want to know what I'm a devil for. Believe me.
The ox makes you uneasy. Try to discern why.
I'm glad you think so. Otherwise, things might've gotten very messy.
*Hnr!*
I suppose I did. Y-yes, I had quite a life in Elturel. Chewing cud. Pulling carts. Et cetera.
Did you come from Elturel with the others?
*Something's off. This creature isn't what it appears to be.*
Ah, you're addressing me. A humble ox. How... quaint.
There's more to you than meets the eye. Care to explain?
Come on, old chap. I'm a devil for gossip.

Synopsis: The player comes across some ox in the Tieflings cave at Druid's Grove. The player may notice the ox acting strangely.
